{#
  hx-split-panel — Drupal Twig Template
  ========================================
  Renders the <hx-split-panel> web component for use in Drupal themes.

  A resizable two-pane layout with a draggable divider. Drag interaction,
  keyboard navigation (Arrow keys, Page Up/Down, Home, End), and ARIA
  semantics are handled by the component.

  Attribute compatibility:
    All public properties are attribute-settable from Twig. The `snap` property
    accepts a JSON array string (e.g. snap="[25, 50, 75]") which the component
    parses automatically. See P1-06 in AUDIT.md — this was fixed with a custom
    converter.

  Variables:
    - position           (number, optional): Initial divider position as a
                         percentage of the start panel (0–100). Defaults to 50.
    - position_in_pixels (number, optional): Alternative to `position`. Sets
                         the initial divider position in pixels. Converted to
                         a percentage on first render. Takes precedence over
                         `position` until the host is measured.
    - orientation        (string, optional): 'horizontal' (default) or 'vertical'.
                         Horizontal split = left/right panes.
                         Vertical split = top/bottom panes.
    - min                (number, optional): Minimum divider position as a
                         percentage. Defaults to 0.
    - max                (number, optional): Maximum divider position as a
                         percentage. Defaults to 100.
    - snap               (string, optional): JSON array of snap-point percentages.
                         Example: '[25, 50, 75]'
                         The divider snaps to the nearest point within 5%.
    - disabled           (boolean, optional): Locks the divider; prevents dragging
                         and keyboard repositioning.
    - start_content      (string, optional): HTML/Twig markup for the start panel.
                         Rendered in the `start` slot.
    - end_content        (string, optional): HTML/Twig markup for the end panel.
                         Rendered in the `end` slot.
    - attributes         (object, optional): Additional HTML attributes.

  CSS parts (for theming):
    - start   — The start panel container.
    - divider — The draggable divider element.
    - end     — The end panel container.

  Events:
    hx-reposition — Dispatched when the divider is moved.
                    Detail: { position: number } (percentage)

  Usage:

    Basic horizontal split (left navigation / content area):
      {% include 'hx-split-panel.twig' with {
        position: 30,
        min: 15,
        max: 70,
        start_content: '<nav>' ~ drupal_menu('main') ~ '</nav>',
        end_content: node.body.value,
      } %}

    Vertical split (header / body panes):
      {% include 'hx-split-panel.twig' with {
        orientation: 'vertical',
        position: 25,
        start_content: '<header>' ~ page.header ~ '</header>',
        end_content: '<main>' ~ page.content ~ '</main>',
      } %}

    Patient record layout with snap points:
      {% include 'hx-split-panel.twig' with {
        position: 50,
        snap: '[25, 50, 75]',
        min: 20,
        max: 80,
        start_content: patient_summary_html,
        end_content: patient_detail_html,
      } %}

    Fixed pixel initial position:
      {% include 'hx-split-panel.twig' with {
        position_in_pixels: 300,
        start_content: sidebar_html,
        end_content: main_html,
      } %}

    Locked (non-resizable) layout:
      {% include 'hx-split-panel.twig' with {
        position: 40,
        disabled: true,
        start_content: sidebar_html,
        end_content: content_html,
      } %}

  Registration:
    Load the component script in your theme's .libraries.yml:
      hx-split-panel:
        js:
          path/to/@helixui/library/dist/hx-split-panel.js: { attributes: { type: module } }

    Attach the library in your template:
      {{ attach_library('mytheme/hx-split-panel') }}

  Responding to resize events in Drupal:
    Listen for hx-reposition to save panel state (e.g., persist to localStorage):

      (function (Drupal, once) {
        Drupal.behaviors.helixSplitPanel = {
          attach: function (context) {
            once('hx-split-panel', 'hx-split-panel[data-persist-key]', context).forEach((el) => {
              var key = el.dataset.persistKey;
              var saved = localStorage.getItem('hx-split-panel:' + key);
              if (saved !== null) { el.position = parseFloat(saved); }
              el.addEventListener('hx-reposition', function (e) {
                localStorage.setItem('hx-split-panel:' + key, e.detail.position);
              });
            });
          },
        };
      })(Drupal, once);
#}

{% set _position = position|default(50) %}
{% set _orientation = orientation|default('horizontal') %}
{% set _min = min|default(0) %}
{% set _max = max|default(100) %}

<hx-split-panel
  position="{{ _position }}"
  orientation="{{ _orientation }}"
  min="{{ _min }}"
  max="{{ _max }}"
  {% if position_in_pixels is defined and position_in_pixels %}position-in-pixels="{{ position_in_pixels }}"{% endif %}
  {% if snap %}snap="{{ snap }}"{% endif %}
  {% if disabled %}disabled{% endif %}
  {% if attributes %}{% for key, val in attributes %}{{ key }}="{{ val }}" {% endfor %}{% endif %}
>
  {%- if start_content is defined -%}
    <div slot="start">{{ start_content }}</div>
  {%- endif -%}
  {%- if end_content is defined -%}
    <div slot="end">{{ end_content }}</div>
  {%- endif -%}
</hx-split-panel>
